# Fe II photoionization cross-sections for ATLAS12
#
# Source: Opacity Project R-matrix calculation,
#         Nahar & Pradhan (1994), J. Phys. B 27, 429
# Via:    TLUSTY model atom (Hubeny & Lanz 2017, arXiv:1706.01937)
#
# Format (TLUSTY OP fit-point convention, User's Guide sec. 11.2):
#   header:   NLEV
#   levels:   ilev  g_stat  nu_threshold[Hz]  'label'
#   bf data:  ilev  ifancy  nfit
#             nfit pairs of (x, log10(sigma_Mb))
#             where x = log10(nu/nu_threshold)
#             and sigma is the photoionization cross-section in Mb.
#             For ifancy=2: a single Seaton-form record
#             s0  alpha  beta  gamma
#             with sigma(nu) [Mb] = s0 * [beta + (1-beta)*(nu_th/nu)^gamma]
#                                 * (nu_th/nu)^alpha
#             (s0 itself is in Mb; multiply by 1e-18 cm^2/Mb for cgs.)
#
# Pseudo-levels representing Fe III in the source file
# have been removed; only true Fe II bound levels are retained.
#
